INSERT INTO notes VALUES('64ce4aaf-fcb4-47ad-9ab4-8c9b3a67ccf7','What is your favourite futuristic technology and why?',replace('Virtual Reality is projected to grow exponentially in next five years. Virtual Reality (VR) and Augmented Reality (AR) are two technologies that have the potential to significantly change the world in which we live. However, currently they are struggling to truly capture the hearts and minds of consumers and businesses. Mixed and merged reality can be seen as subsets or supersets of the VR and AR headset categories.The main reason is that these devices basically overlay graphics onto real or virtual worlds which creates almost a illusion to what we perceive. The main applications for VR today are gaming and immersive (360°) video playback. While gaming is also an application for AR, the focus of AR is more on professional and educational use cases. These AR and VR have the capability that they can replace the mobile phones which we are using now.\nthat''s why as per my perception AR and VR which combinely Mixed reality will rule the future world.','\n',char(10)),'2022-12-15 01:44:37',NULL,'');
