INSERT INTO notes VALUES('d004ec7c-f248-4100-8937-8774eadae38e','Precision and Recall',replace('https://in.coursera.org/learn/advanced-learning-algorithms/lecture/pjuBJ/error-metrics-for-skewed-datasets\n\nMostly in skewed datasets\n\n(upside actual class and downside predicted class)\n        1             0       Actual\n|--------------|---------------|\n|      TP     |     FP       | 1          Predicted\n|---------------|--------------|\n|       FN    |    TN       | 0\n|--------------|---------------|\nPrecision: Of all patients we predicted y=1, what fraction of them actually have rare disease?\nIt is ratio of actual and predicted positive to the predicted positive.\nPrecision = TP/(TP + FP)\n\nIt is wrt to predicted class\n\nRecall: Of all patients that actually have the rare disease, what fraction of them did we correctly detect having that rare disease?\n\nRecall = TP/(TP+FN)\n\nIt is wrt to actual class\n\nAlgorithm with 0 precision and 0 recall is not a useful algorithm.\n\nMake sure that both precision and recall as higher values in rare classes that is reasonably very helpful.\n\nAnother insight in image above about precision and recall (Actual class in both examples won''t affect if we increase the threshold)\n\nWe need to balance between FP and FN\nhttps://in.coursera.org/learn/advanced-learning-algorithms/lecture/42TEG/trading-off-precision-and-recall','\n',char(10)),'2023-03-10 16:18:06',NULL,'');
