INSERT INTO notes VALUES('b05b74a5-7c9d-408c-9f48-cf77e15064e1','Preference based route navigation considering Capacity and Order of Delivery-Pickup',replace('As we know that due to growth of online ecommerce websites like Amazon, Flipkart, Myntra they serve almost 2 to 2.5 million order per day (which is a huge number). There orders We Can be both deliveries and pickups on well. (Pickups may be few). The delivery partners in this play a key role (to make fulfillment of user). These orders were properly channeled in such a way that to reach the destination. Now, consider, from every depot they have a certain limit and stops but stops may vary over a Period.\n\nNow coming to the problem statement it is a general Problem facing by the depot such that they have fleet of Vehicles, each day set of Customos and they have to deliver and Pickup of the goods It is a VRP problem and drivers and planners don''t satisfy with the VRP solution became drivers Considers other facting like Parking space, lunch & rest place and the things The drivers have the implicit preferences (or) Knowledge about there things and it is not easy to put it into VRP formulation is almost importable. (In general plannen modity the routes to meet the expectation of driver)\n\n→ The goal is to respect / keep the preferences they drive into account along with the Simultaneous delivery and pickup of goods Keeping the vehicle Comtraints is a challenging task.\n\n→ Another challenge adaptability of the Solution to learn their preferences and the Over the time. (according to preferences)\n\nPreferences modelled using the maximum likelihood routing of first order Markov model and then the feature variables like particular day of the week,set of stops,past stops acts as latent features and taken as the  feature variables along with the preferences provides as transition probabilities computed by Markov counting approach and giving these feature variables to nn using cross entropy loss and decision focused loss then calculating the performance metrics with respect to arc difference (minimal changes made to convert predicted route to actual route) and route difference (number of edges traversed in actual but not in predicted solution)','\n',char(10)),'2022-12-14 22:16:13',NULL,'');
