INSERT INTO notes VALUES('01fa13c9-09df-4180-9b58-08aa6b2acca9','',replace('study about convex functions\nHow we show that any function is convex or not? (multiple variables) -- using hessian\n\nFor convex function f"(x)>=0 at all domain points.\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nZ7vjo2dQ1o\n\nhttps://math.stackexchange.com/questions/1582452/logistic-regression-prove-that-the-cost-function-is-convex\n\nsum of two convex functions is also convex\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nsigmoid and logistic function same(contextually)\nhttps://towardsdatascience.com/understanding-sigmoid-logistic-softmax-functions-and-cross-entropy-loss-log-loss-dbbbe0a17efb\n\nThe most common sigmoid function used in machine learning is Logistic Function.\nf(x)=1/(1+exp(-x))\n\nFor logistic regression, f(x) is the sigmoid (logistic) function, whereas for linear regression, f(x) is a linear function.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nAdvanced Learning Algorithms\n\nActivations are used in higher level features\n\nActivations are used as the input to higher-level neurons(deeper layers), which learn to recognize more abstract and complex features\n\nMeaning is :\n\n(Not exactly same)\nActivations are used to extract high level features in the network layer (i.e. from the layer if it crosses the threshold then it triggers) as like affordability, quality features which have high impact as shown in the T-shirt demand prediction example which have higher impact(so called high level features)....','\n',char(10)),'2023-02-19 13:17:16',NULL,'');
